cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to image processing and color correction, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques, such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), further supports this classification. Additionally, the paper involves the development of a novel framework for illuminant estimation, which could potentially fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of clustering-based iterative fitting also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the development of a new dataset for illuminant estimation, which could potentially fall under the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
